<h1><span style="font-size:28px;"><strong>Rulers of the Castle</strong></span></h1>

<hr />
<h3><strong>Residence Hall Director:</strong>&nbsp;</h3>

<p>The Residence Hall Director is a full-time professional staff member who oversees the day-to-day operations, safety, and security of the community, theater, and shops. More specifically, the Residence Hall Director with support from the Assistant Hall Director and Resident Advisors:&nbsp;</p>

<ul>
	<li>Provides community and program development, administrative management, and general counseling for their respective communities.&nbsp;</li>
	<li>Supports enforcement of <a href="https://www.dfa.cornell.edu/policy/policies/campus-code-conduct">university policies</a> and <a href="https://living.sas.cornell.edu/live/movingin/upload/House-Rules-17-18-Final.pdf">house rules</a>.</li>
	<li>Facilities and supports faculty-student interactions and student development for their respective communities.&nbsp;</li>
	<li>Selects, supervises, trains, and evaluates staff members.</li>
	<li>Participates in department and university committees and initiatives.</li>
</ul>

<p><span style="font-size:18px;"><strong>Meet your Residence Hall Director Evan!</strong></span></p>

<p><img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/os-content-uploads/290573ba-31e3-44c6-85af-3b4d1758392a.jpg" style="height: 300px; width: 300px;" /></p>

<p>This is Evan&#39;s first year at Cornell and as a Residence Hall Director in Risley. Originally from a small town in Connecticut, Evan has always had a passion for the arts taking multiple arts classes during his undergraduate career and attending acting school in New York City in his youth. Evan performed in plays and variety shows during his youth, his most notable being the Scarecrow in &quot;The Wizard of Oz&quot;. Evan is thrilled to be apart of the Risley community and works hard to ensure the success of every Risleyite!&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;<em>Education:</em>&nbsp;B.S. Communications, Eastern Connecticut State University &amp; M.A. Higher Education and Student Affairs, The Ohio State University.</p>

