<p><img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/os-content-uploads/7fab6224-7422-46d0-83de-b8b29d576e4f.jpg" style="height: 400px; width: 300px;" /></p>

<p>Hi everyone! My name is Kelvin Polanco and I was born and raised in New York City in the Manhattan&rsquo;s gem of a neighborhood, Washington Heights. I graduated from Cornell in 2015 with a B.S. in Biology and Society and I&rsquo;m back on campus pursuing my Master&rsquo;s in Healthcare Administration. As far as hobbies go, I love taking photos, I coach Little League Baseball and I can sit down and watch basketball for hours. I love meeting new people and hearing their stories so feel free to swing by if you ever want to chat. It&rsquo;s a pleasure to live and share this space with you all!<em>&nbsp;</em></p>

<hr />
<p><strong><span style="font-size:16px;">Resident Advisors</span></strong></p>

<p>Resident Advisors are integral to the success of the residential community. They are strong undergraduate leaders who:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Serve as a peer counselor, community builder, academic resource, programmer and administrator.</li>
	<li>Create floor and hall community.</li>
	<li>Responsible for their residents and are sensitive to the needs of their community.</li>
	<li>Encourage&nbsp;and foster&nbsp;resident involvement, respect, and engagement.</li>
	<li>Enforce university policies and house rules.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>

<h2><strong>Meet your Resident Advisors! (2017-2018)</strong></h2>

<p><strong>Lydia Caroe</strong></p>

