<p>&quot;I am from Las Cruces, New Mexico and I am the seventh of eight kids in my family. I attended a performing arts high school where I studied traditional Flamenco dance. I am currently a Sophomore studying Hotel Administration in the hopes of opening an Inn on P.E.I, Canada.&nbsp; When I am not in my room studying or binging Netflix, you can find me at Statler or grabbing the greatest ice cream in America at the Dairy Bar. In addition to various hotel clubs, I am also a Community Group leader for Cru Student Ministries. I love plants, puppies, hiking, peanut butter, coffee, and the slap happy laughter of late nights. Most of all, I love the arts and whether a genuine thespian or a creativity novice, I look forward to the opportunity to grow with others in a community that values self-discovery and artistic expression.&quot;</p>

